				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\gamma (\lambda ) = \frac{1}{L}\ln \left( {\frac{{T_1(\lambda )}}{{T_2(\lambda )}}} \right)$$\end{document}where T1(λ) and T2(λ) are the measured transmitted spectra of the SLD with and without solar illumination, respectively; and L is the length of the fiber. A significant amount of luminescence was produced by the excited Nd3+ ions, which masked the SLD T1 signal. This luminescence signal was subtracted in the calculations after being separately measured with the SLD turned off.
